{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Subsidise the conversion of Euro 5 diesel engines to Euro 6.",
        "additional_details": "We call on the government to support them by subsidising Euro 6 retrofits. This would benefit those on low income & British business.\r\n \r\nWe support the pollution-reduction aims of Clean Air Zones and ULEZ expansion.\r\n \r\nHowever, the speed with which these policies have been introduced has disproportionately affected lower-income people.\r\n \r\nUK-based businesses can retro-fit older vehicles to meet Euro 6 standards.\r\n \r\nHowever, the cost is prohibitive for many people.\r\n \r\nSubsidising this would benefit those on low incomes, British business, and reduce opposition to further environmental policy revisions.",
        "background": "Clean Air Zones & ULEZ expansion will reduce pollution. However, many lower-income people suddenly face huge daily running costs & devaluation of their vehicle.",
